          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Investigation of the scattering cross sections of",
                "neutrons on carbon nuclei at the reactor filtered beams"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "4UKRIJD"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Reactor WWR-M"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron filters installed in horizontal channel",
                "of the reactor."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "1) Filter 2 keV.  Average energy of filtered neutron",
                " (1.91 (+0.69,-0.86))keV (95% response function),",
                "the filter components (g/cm2):   Sc-110.59, Ni60-80.2,",
                "Fe54-39.37, S-55.7, Co-26.7, 10B(85%)-0.2.",
                "Purity of the filter - 99.6 %. Other additions to the",
                "main neutron line were about: a line with the energy",
                "26.7keV - 0.1%, 42.8keV - 0.15%, 49.0keV - 0.02%,",
                "64.6keV  - 0.13%.",
                "2) Filter 3.5 keV.  Average energy of filtered neutron",
                " (3.471 (+1.076,-1.69))keV (95% response function),",
                "the filter components (g/cm2): Cd-0.865, 10B-3.15,",
                "         60Ni-146.2, 54Fe-170.7, Al-1.349, S-36.7.",
                "Purity of beam about 96.8%, other additions to",
                "the main line were: 43 keV - 0.4%, 65 keV - 1.2%,",
                "86 keV - 0.2%.",
                "3) Filter 24 keV.  Average energy of filtered neutron",
                " (23.85 (+1.26,-2.51))keV (95% response function),",
                "the filter components (g/cm2):   S-16.35, Fe-236.1,",
                "                             Al-99.86, 10B(85%)-0.95.",
                "Purity of the filter - 98.7 %. Other additions to the",
                "main neutron line were about: a line with the energy",
                "274keV - 0.4%, 350keV - 0.2%, 610keV - 0.1%.",
                "4) Filter 134 keV. Average energy of filtered neutron",
                " (133.894 (+1.536,-2.424)keV (95% response function),",
                "the filter components (g/cm2):  58Ni-194.01, 60Ni-3.12,",
                " 10B-0.2, Si-93.08, Cr52-95.94).",
                "Purity of beam about 99.35%, other additions to",
                "the main spectra were: 121 keV-0.004%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FNB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PROPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detector consisting of 3He counters",
                " (58 units), was located just above the carbon samples.",
                "The 3He counters (CHM-37, 7 atm, diameter=18 mm, L=50",
                "cm) are placed in five layers (12 or 11 in each layer).",
                "The detector was covered by cadmium sheet with",
                "thickness 0.5 mm; it was protected then by borated",
                "polyethylene bricks."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "From two to four carbon samples were used for",
                "measurements at each energy. The samples are a set of",
                "carbon disks (from one to four units), each with a",
                "thickness of 1 mm and a diameter of 30.4 mm(C 99.997%).",
                "These carbon disks were made by GoodFellow Cambridge",
                "Limited Company (England).",
                "1) Filter 2 keV. Four samples thick: 0.008877+-1.2E-05,",
                "0.017753+-2.4E-05, 0.02663+-3.6E-05,",
                "0.035507+-4.8E-05 atom/b.",
                "2) Filter 3.5 keV. Two samples thick: 0.008877+-1.2E-05",
                "and 0.02663+-3.6E-05 atom/b.",
                "3) Filter 24 keV. Two samples thick: 0.017753+-2.4E-05,",
                "and 0.02663+-3.6E-05 atom/b.",
                "4) Filters 133 keV. Three samples thick: 0.008877+-",
                "1.2E-05, 0.017753+-2.4E-05, 0.02663+-3.6E-05 atom/b."
              ]
            }
          ],
